Interacting Arms¶

We can see that it's difficult to generate Purcell strokes for $\phi > 2$ due to the hydrodynamic interactions between the arms.

import numpy as np
import scipy as sp
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns; sns.set(); sns.set_style("whitegrid")
plt.rcParams["animation.html"] = "jshtml"
from celluloid import Camera
import stokeslets as slts
import purcell as pur

figfile = "figs/"

et = 2
ph = 2.5
expected = np.poly1d(pur.fit()[0]) #fit for power required
s,r,tim = pur.init(et,ph,T=4)
tau = pur.stroke_input(expected(ph),tim,r,strokes=0.5)
R = slts.mesher()
_,pswimmer = slts.evolve(tau,tim,R,r,s,k=100,e=0.3,c=0.6)

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (4.5,4.5))
plt.xlim(-1,1); plt.ylim(-1,1)
camera = Camera(fig)
for i in range(0,np.shape(pswimmer)[0],8):
    plt.plot(pswimmer[i].T[0],pswimmer[i].T[1],'k-', linewidth=2, alpha=0.5, label='_nolegend_')
    plt.plot(np.mean(pswimmer[i].T[0]),np.mean(pswimmer[i].T[1]),'ro', linewidth=2, alpha=0.5)
    camera.snap()
plt.legend(["CoM"])
plt.close()

animation = camera.animate()
animation.save(figfile+"interacting_arms.gif",writer = 'imagemagick',fps = 10,dpi=300)
animation

Dragging Body¶

It's not possible to work in a regime with $\eta <= 1$ due to the issue of the body being dragged by the action of the motor preventing any net angular displacement of the arm relative to the body.

et = 1
ph = np.pi/3
s,r,tim = pur.init(et,ph,T=4)
tau = pur.stroke_input(0.5,tim,r,strokes=0.5) #tiny amount of power
R = slts.mesher()
_,pswimmer = slts.evolve(tau,tim,R,r,s,k=100,e=0.3,c=0.6)

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (4.5,4.5))
plt.xlim(-1,1); plt.ylim(-1,1)
camera = Camera(fig)
for i in range(0,np.shape(pswimmer)[0],8):
    plt.plot(pswimmer[i].T[0],pswimmer[i].T[1],'k-', linewidth=2, alpha=0.5, label='_nolegend_')
    plt.plot(np.mean(pswimmer[i].T[0]),np.mean(pswimmer[i].T[1]),'ro', linewidth=2, alpha=0.5)
    camera.snap()
plt.legend(["CoM"])
plt.close()

animation = camera.animate()
animation.save(figfile+"dragging_body.gif",writer = 'imagemagick',fps = 10,dpi=300)
animation
